 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
                  Makefiles for the AENET Package
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------

 Compile from the main 'src' directory with:

   make -f ./makefiles/MAKEFILE

 where MAKEFILE is one of the files listed below.

 GNU Fortran Compiler
 --------------------

 Most GFortran Makefiles are compatible with Linux and MacOS.  For those
 that link with the Intel MKL, separate MacOS-only Makefiles are needed
 ("_MacOS" appended to file name).

 Makefile.gfortran_serial          - Serial version using system BLAS
                                     and LAPACK libraries
 Makefile.gfortran_openblas_serial - Serial version using the OpenBLAS
                                     library
 Makefile.gfortran_mkl_serial      - Serial version using the Intel Math
                                     Kernel Library (MKL)

 Makefile.gfortran_mpi             - OpenMPI parallelized; using LAPACK/BLAS
 Makefile.gfortran_openblas_mpi    - OpenMPI; using OpenBLAS
 Makefile.gfortran_mkl_mpi         - OpenMPI; using Intel MKL

 Makefile.gfortran_debug           - Debugging flags activated
 Makefile.gfortran_mpi_debug       - OpenMPI; Debugging flags activated

 Intel Fortran Compiler + Math Kernel Library (MKL)
 --------------------------------------------------

 Makefile.ifort_serial      - Serial version
 Makefile.ifort_mpi         - OpenMPI parallelization
 Makefile.ifort_intelmpi    - Intel MPI

